  "title": "CHIEF OPERATING OFFICER (COO)",
  "description": "<p><!--td {border: 1px solid #cccccc;}br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}--></p><p>Lead and oversee the day-to-day operations of the company, ensuring alignment with strategic goals and long-term vision.</p><p>Partner closely with the CEO and executive team to formulate and execute strategic initiatives across multiple business units.</p><p>Manage and optimize functions such as Sales, HR, Finance, Operations, Technology, and Customer Success.</p><p>Develop scalable systems, workflows, and performance metrics to support rapid growth and operational excellence.</p><p>Drive cost-efficiency, resource allocation, and budget control across departments.</p><p>Build a high-performing leadership team through mentorship, accountability, and continuous development.</p><p>Monitor and assess operational risks and implement mitigation frameworks to safeguard the business.</p><p>Represent the company in strategic meetings, stakeholder discussions, and board-level reporting.</p><p>Lead change management, digital transformation, and process optimization projects as needed.</p><p>Willingness to work night shift and split shift.</p><p>Willingness to work extra hours or weekend if needed.</p>",
